dc_description_s: These data layers represent zoning for Sheboygan County, Wisconsin in 2016. It is a feature class within the geodatabase “Sheboygan_Zoning_2016.gdb”. The features included in this geodatabase are “FARMLAND”, “FLOODPLAIN”, and “SHORELAND”. [Farmland: This data shows land in Sheboygan County that is in or out of the County FPA. Floodplain: Sheboygan County Floodplain data - revised April 21, 2009. Includes LOMR for Belgium-Holland Drainage District.]
uw_supplemental_s: This is an archived copy of the data held at UW-Madison. For the most recent version of this data please visit: https://geospatialhub-shebco.hub.arcgis.com/pages/open-data.
